\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. B. tectorum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 77 (1753). Stems 5-90 cm, erect, slender, glabrous or slightly puberulent. Leaves 4-16 cm × 2-4 mm, softly hairy; lower sheaths hairy, the upper sometimes glabrous. Panicle 5-20 cm, lax or rather dense, at first erect, then nodding and mostly secund, often pale green tinged with purple, shining when glabrous; branches slender, hairy, flexuous, with up to 8 spikelets; spikelets 10-20 × 3-4 mm, nodding, narrow at first, becoming cuneate when ripe, with 4-8 florets, hairy or glabrous. Glumes with hyaline margins, the lower 5-8(-9) mm, the upper 7-11(-13) mm. Lemma 9-12 × 2-3 mm, lanceolate; awn 10-18 mm, slender, straight. Palea distinctly shorter than lemma. Stamens 3; anthers 0·5-1 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Europe, northwards to N. France, S. Fennoscandia and C. Russia.} ?Al Au Be Bu Co Cr Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Sa Si Su Tu [Br Fe Rs (B)].
