\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. B. fasciculatus} C. Presl,{\i  Cyper. Gram. Sic.} 39 (1820). Stems 4-25 cm, erect or geniculate at base, sometimes hairy below the panicle. Leaves and sheaths softly hairy, the lamina 2-10 cm × 1-2 mm. Panicle 4-5 × 0·7-1·2 cm, stiffly erect; branches rigid, shorter than the spikelets, glabrous or hairy; spikelets 20-30 mm (excluding awns), broadly cuneate. Lower glume 7-8 mm, subulate, the upper 12-14 mm, narrowly lanceolate. Lemma 13-15 × 1-1·5 mm, with somewhat incurved margins, glabrous or hairy, gently curved outwards at maturity, deeply emarginate at the apex; awn 13-18 mm, about equalling the lemma, rough, straight or slightly divaricate. Palea shorter than lemma. Stamens 3; anthers 0·5-4 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  S. Greece, S. Italy and islands of the Mediterranean region.} Bl Co Cr Gr It Sa Si.
