\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. B. rubens} L.,{\i  Cent. Pl.}{\b  1}: 5 (1755). Stems 10-40 cm, erect or ascending, glabrous below, often hairy below the inflorescence. Leaves up to 12 cm × 5 mm, flat, hairy; sheaths softly pubescent. Panicle 2-10 × 2-5 cm, erect, very dense, cuneate at base, often reddish-brown; branches and pedicels much shorter than the spikelets, pubescent; spikelets 18-25 × 2-6 mm, cuneate, hairy or glabrous, subsessile, with 4-8 florets. Lower glume 5-7 mm, subulate, the upper 8-10 mm, lanceolate, both with wide, hyaline margins. Lemma 10-13 × 2-3 mm, oblong-elliptical, strongly veined and 2-fid for c. 4 mm; awn 8-12 mm, straight, reddish. Palea shorter than lemma, very narrow. Stamens 2 or 3; anthers 0·5-1 mm. 2n = 28.{\i  Mediterranean region and S.W. Europe.} ?Az Bl Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Lu Sa Si Tu.
